cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.AL 

This paper deals with the problem of embedding service chains in a network, which is a topic related to network virtualization and software-defined networking (SDN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the classic virtual network embedding problem, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel extension of linear programming and randomized rounding technique, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of algorithms and complexity, hence cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which could be relevant to the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
